In the Matter of The Petition of Edward E. CUMMINGS, Appellee. In re Joseph BASS, Appellant. No. 181. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 13, 1936. T. Louis A. Britt, of New York City (Charles J. Carroll, of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Alexander, Ash & Jones, of New York City (Lawson R. Jones and Edward Ash, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
